  "response": "Both BCom and MCom can be suitable for pursuing an MBA in Europe, but an MCom might offer some advantages:\n\nMCom Advantages:\n1. More advanced academic qualification\n2. Deeper business and commerce knowledge\n3. Better research skills\n4. Potentially higher chances of MBA admission\n5. Might provide more competitive profile for European universities\n\nBCom Advantages:\n1. Shorter duration of study\n2. Lower cost of education\n3. Can work earlier\n4. Practical business foundation\n\nRecommended steps:\n1. Check specific MBA program requirements\n2. Consider your professional goals\n3. Research European university admission criteria\n4. Look into specific university preferences\n5. Consider work experience alongside academic qualification\n\nFactors to consider:\n- Your engineering background\n- Specific MBA program requirements\n- Your career objectives\n- Individual university admission criteria\n\nOverall, while an MCom might provide a slight edge, your work experience, entrance exam scores (GMAT/GRE), and overall profile are equally important for MBA admissions in Europe.\n\nSuggestion: Directly consult target universities about their specific admission requirements.",
